subject: Gmail update: Reach more people you know
body:
Ever wanted to email someone you know, but haven't yet exchanged email  
addresses? Starting this week, when you're composing a new email, Gmail  
will suggest your Google+ connections as recipients, even if you haven't  
exchanged email addresses yet.

How it works with email addresses
Emailing Google+ connections works a bit differently to protect the privacy  
of email addresses. Your email address isn't visible to your Google+  
connections until you send them an email, and their email addresses are not  
visible to you until they respond.

Receiving email from people outside your circles [link:  
https://support.google.com/plus/answer/1047805?hl=en_US]
If you receive an email from someone outside your circles, it will be  
filtered into the Social category of the inbox [link:  
https://support.google.com/mail/answer/3094596?hl=en_US](if enabled) and  
only after you respond or add them to your circles, can they start another  
conversation with you.

How to control who can contact you
You're in control of whether people can reach you with a new setting in  
Gmail [link: https://mail.google.com/mail/#settings/general] on the  
desktop. To learn more, check out the Help Center [link:  
https://support.google.com/mail/?p=profiles&hl=en_US].
